@startuml 02_domain_communication
!theme plain

title Level 1: Domain Communication Architecture\nHyundai/Mobis Standard Network Topology

skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor LightBlue
    BorderColor DarkBlue
    ArrowColor DarkGreen
}

package "Powertrain Domain" as PT #LightYellow {
    [EMS] as EMS
    [TCU] as TCU
    [OPI] as OPI
    [LPI] as LPI
    [FPCM] as FPCM
}

package "Chassis Domain" as CH #LightGreen {
    [ESP] as ESP
    [ABS] as ABS
    [MDPS] as MDPS
    [SAS] as SAS
    [EPB] as EPB
    [ECS] as ECS
}

package "ADAS Domain" as AD #LightCyan {
    [F_CAMERA] as CAM
    [BSD_RADAR] as BSD
    [SCC] as SCC
    [SPAS] as SPAS
    [AVM] as AVM
}

package "Body Domain" as BD #LightPink {
    [BCM] as BCM
    [DATC] as DATC
    [FATC] as FATC
    [TPMS] as TPMS
    [SMK] as SMK
}

package "Infotainment Domain" as IT #LightSalmon {
    [IVI] as IVI
    [CLU] as CLU
    [HUD] as HUD
    [TMU] as TMU
}

package "Safety Domain" as SF #Tomato {
    [ACU] as ACU
    [ODS] as ODS
}

component "Central Gateway\n(CGW)" as CGW #Gold

' CAN-HS #1 Network (Powertrain + Chassis + Safety)
cloud "CAN-HS #1\n500 kbps" as CAN1 #LightGray

EMS --> CAN1 : Vehicle Speed\nEngine RPM\nTorque
TCU --> CAN1 : Gear Position\nShift Request
ESP --> CAN1 : Stability Status\nBrake Request
ABS --> CAN1 : Wheel Speed\nBrake Pressure
MDPS --> CAN1 : Steering Angle\nSteering Torque
ACU --> CAN1 : Airbag Status\nCrash Detection

CAN1 --> CGW : Route to\nother networks

' CAN-HS #2 Network (ADAS + Infotainment)
cloud "CAN-HS #2\n500 kbps" as CAN2 #LightGray

CAM --> CAN2 : LDW Warning\nLKA Status\nLane Detection
BSD --> CAN2 : Blind Spot\nWarning
SCC --> CAN2 : Cruise Control\nSpeed Target
IVI --> CAN2 : Media Info\nAmbient Light ⭐
CLU --> CAN2 : Display Data\nWarning Lights
HUD --> CAN2 : Speed Display\nNavigation

CAN2 --> CGW : Route to\nother networks

' CAN-LS Network (Body)
cloud "CAN-LS\n125 kbps" as CAN3 #LightGray

BCM --> CAN3 : Door Status\nLight Status\nAmbient Feedback ⭐
DATC --> CAN3 : Climate Control\nTemperature
TPMS --> CAN3 : Tire Pressure\nWarning
SMK --> CAN3 : Key Status\nImmobilizer

CAN3 --> CGW : Route to\nother networks

' Gateway Routing
CGW --> CAN1 : Filtered\nMessages
CGW --> CAN2 : Filtered\nMessages
CGW --> CAN3 : Filtered\nMessages

note right of CGW
  **Gateway Routing Rules**

  CAN-HS #1 → CAN-HS #2:
  • Vehicle Speed (EMS → CLU)
  • Engine Status (EMS → IVI)

  CAN-HS #2 → CAN-LS:
  • Ambient Light (IVI → BCM) ⭐
  • User Settings (IVI → BCM)

  CAN-HS #1 → CAN-LS:
  • ESP Status (ESP → BCM)
  • Safety Warnings (ACU → BCM)

  **Security**:
  • Message filtering
  • Authentication
  • Firewall rules
end note

note bottom of PT
  **Powertrain Domain**
  • Real-time critical (10-100ms)
  • ASIL-D safety level
  • High-priority messages
end note

note bottom of AD
  **ADAS Domain**
  • Sensor fusion
  • High bandwidth
  • ASIL-B/C safety level
end note

note bottom of BD
  **Body Domain**
  • Comfort features
  • Lower priority
  • Event-driven messages
end note

legend right
  **Network Characteristics**

  CAN-HS #1 (500 kbps):
  • Powertrain + Chassis + Safety
  • Safety-critical messages
  • High-speed, low-latency

  CAN-HS #2 (500 kbps):
  • ADAS + Infotainment
  • User interface
  • Sensor data

  CAN-LS (125 kbps):
  • Body + Comfort
  • Non-critical messages
  • Event-driven

  ⭐ = Project-specific feature
endlegend

@enduml
